results.name: Squares divisible by more than one cube > 1.
link: Hugo Pfoertner, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
example: a(1) = 64 because 16^2 is divisible by 2^3 and by 4^3.
program: (PARI) iscubes(n) = {my(nb = 0); fordiv(n, d, if ((d>1) && ispower(d, 3), nb++; if (nb > 1, return(1))););}
results.author: _Hugo Pfoertner_, Oct 27 2018
